{"article_id":"FEF5KncYM5R21DCR","edus":[{"id":0,"text":"House Speaker John A. Boehner offered the first olive branch Wednesday in what is expected to be a frenetic spate of postelection deal-making","depth":3},{"id":1,"text":"to avert the looming \" fiscal cliff , \"","depth":3},{"id":2,"text":"saying","depth":3},{"id":3,"text":"the GOP will let the government collect more tax revenue","depth":4},{"id":4,"text":"if President Obama will drop his plan","depth":5},{"id":5,"text":"to raise tax rates on the wealthy .","depth":5},{"id":6,"text":"Voters on Tuesday re-elected Mr. Obama","depth":6},{"id":7,"text":"and expanded Democrats ' majority in the Senate ,","depth":7},{"id":8,"text":"while keeping Republicans in charge of the House","depth":8},{"id":9,"text":"- albeit with fewer numbers .","depth":8},{"id":10,"text":"With the needle tilting slightly but decidedly toward Democrats ,","depth":6},{"id":11,"text":"Mr. Boehner ' s overture sets the stage for the lame-duck session of Congress ,","depth":8},{"id":12,"text":"which begins next week ,","depth":8},{"id":13,"text":"and for the full 113th Congress ,","depth":8},{"id":14,"text":"which opens in January .","depth":8},{"id":15,"text":"\" By working together","depth":7},{"id":16,"text":"and creating a fairer , simpler , cleaner tax code ,","depth":7},{"id":17,"text":"we can give our country a stronger , healthier economy .","depth":7},{"id":18,"text":"A stronger economy means more revenue ,","depth":8},{"id":19,"text":"which is what the president seeks , \"","depth":8},{"id":20,"text":"the Republican speaker said .","depth":5},{"id":21,"text":"A day after the election , leaders on all sides said","depth":6},{"id":22,"text":"the message","depth":8},{"id":23,"text":"they took from voters","depth":8},{"id":24,"text":"was that Congress and the White House must work together","depth":8},{"id":25,"text":"to find a solution to the tax increases and automatic spending cuts","depth":9},{"id":26,"text":"that are looming in early January .","depth":9},{"id":27,"text":"\" I know how to fight .","depth":8},{"id":28,"text":"I know how to dance .","depth":9},{"id":29,"text":"I don ' t dance as well","depth":11},{"id":30,"text":"as I fight ,","depth":11},{"id":31,"text":"but I ' d much rather dance anytime , \"","depth":10},{"id":32,"text":"said Senate Majority Leader Harry Reid , a Nevada Democrat","depth":8},{"id":33,"text":"who said","depth":9},{"id":34,"text":"he approached negotiations with an open mind","depth":10},{"id":35,"text":"and wouldn ' t draw any lines in the sand .","depth":10},{"id":36,"text":"Mr. Reid said","depth":9},{"id":37,"text":"he read Tuesday ' s election as a mandate","depth":10},{"id":38,"text":"for raising taxes on the wealthy","depth":11},{"id":39,"text":"- something","depth":12},{"id":40,"text":"Mr. Obama ran on as a centerpiece of his campaign .","depth":12},{"id":41,"text":"\" Look at all the polling .","depth":10},{"id":42,"text":"The vast majority of the American people","depth":13},{"id":43,"text":"- rich , poor -","depth":13},{"id":44,"text":"everybody agrees","depth":12},{"id":45,"text":"that the rich","depth":13},{"id":46,"text":"- richest of the rich -","depth":13},{"id":47,"text":"have to help a little bit , \"","depth":12},{"id":48,"text":"Mr. Reid said .","depth":9},{"id":49,"text":"Mr. Boehner , though , said","depth":9},{"id":50,"text":"Republicans in the House won ' t accept increases in tax rates .","depth":9},{"id":51,"text":"His own proposal relies on cutting out tax loopholes ,","depth":10},{"id":52,"text":"which would bring in more revenue ,","depth":11},{"id":53,"text":"then using that money","depth":12},{"id":54,"text":"to lower income tax rates for everyone .","depth":12},{"id":55,"text":"He argues","depth":10},{"id":56,"text":"that the resulting tax code would be better for economic growth ,","depth":11},{"id":57,"text":"which","depth":13},{"id":58,"text":"he said","depth":13},{"id":59,"text":"would produce more money for the federal government in the long run .","depth":12},{"id":60,"text":"Missing from the public conversation Wednesday was Mr. Obama ,","depth":10},{"id":61,"text":"who is once again the key player in negotiations .","depth":10},{"id":62,"text":"He placed private calls to Mr. Reid and Mr. Boehner , as well as Senate Minority Leader Mitch McConnell and House Minority Leader Nancy Pelosi ,","depth":10},{"id":63,"text":"in which he pleaded for a \" balanced \" approach","depth":11},{"id":64,"text":"to cutting the deficit .","depth":11},{"id":65,"text":"But Mr. Obama did not make any public statements ,","depth":9},{"id":66,"text":"instead leaving Vice President Joseph R. Biden to talk with reporters .","depth":9},{"id":67,"text":"\" On the issue of the tax issue , there was a clear , a clear sort of mandate","depth":10},{"id":68,"text":"about people coming much closer to our view about how to deal with tax policy , \"","depth":10},{"id":69,"text":"he said ,","depth":9},{"id":70,"text":"adding","depth":9},{"id":71,"text":"that he expects \" some real soul searching \" on the part of Republicans","depth":10},{"id":72,"text":"to decide","depth":11},{"id":73,"text":"where they are willing to cooperate .","depth":11},{"id":74,"text":"Part of the problem is that the tools","depth":11},{"id":75,"text":"for cutting big deals in Congress","depth":11},{"id":76,"text":"have calcified in recent years ,","depth":10},{"id":77,"text":"and would need to be restored .","depth":9},{"id":78,"text":"The Senate hasn ' t passed a budget in three years ,","depth":9},{"id":79,"text":"and House Republicans this year have run into trouble","depth":10},{"id":80,"text":"in trying to pass big legislation such as the farm bill .","depth":10},{"id":81,"text":"Each side seems to have concluded","depth":9},{"id":82,"text":"that dealing with the other is tantamount to political death .","depth":9},{"id":83,"text":"Mr. Biden said","depth":10},{"id":84,"text":"one way","depth":12},{"id":85,"text":"to do \" a little confidence building \" between the two sides","depth":12},{"id":86,"text":"was to tackle something easier .","depth":11},{"id":87,"text":"He said","depth":10},{"id":88,"text":"that could come on corporate tax rates ,","depth":11},{"id":89,"text":"which","depth":13},{"id":90,"text":"all sides agree","depth":13},{"id":91,"text":"are too high","depth":13},{"id":92,"text":"and riddled with exceptions .","depth":13},{"id":93,"text":"Unless Congress takes action ,","depth":8},{"id":94,"text":"the George W. Bush-era tax cuts are slated to expire Jan. 1 ,","depth":9},{"id":95,"text":"and a day later $ 110 billion in automatic spending cuts","depth":11},{"id":96,"text":"- the result of last year ' s debt deal -","depth":11},{"id":97,"text":"also will take effect .","depth":10},{"id":98,"text":"Together , they would plunge the U.S. into a short but deep double-dip recession","depth":8},{"id":99,"text":"- though they also would leave the federal budget in much better shape","depth":10},{"id":100,"text":"and would produce a stronger economy by the end of the decade ,","depth":10},{"id":101,"text":"according to the Congressional Budget Office .","depth":9},{"id":102,"text":"Both sides in Congress , though , say","depth":8},{"id":103,"text":"the tax increases and spending cuts are simply too much","depth":9},{"id":104,"text":"to stomach right now .","depth":9},{"id":105,"text":"Democrats on Tuesday expanded their majority to at least 54-45 in the Senate ,","depth":9},{"id":106,"text":"with one senator , Maine independent Angus King , not saying","depth":10},{"id":107,"text":"with which party he will caucus .","depth":10},{"id":108,"text":"In the House , the Republican majority dropped ,","depth":9},{"id":109,"text":"though 10 seats were still to be decided as of Wednesday evening .","depth":9},{"id":110,"text":"In the race for the White House , Mr. Obama ' s 2008 margins dropped in the popular vote and the Electoral College","depth":5},{"id":111,"text":"- and Florida was still too close to call Wednesday .","depth":5},{"id":112,"text":"But","depth":5},{"id":113,"text":"even without Florida ,","depth":6},{"id":114,"text":"Mr. Obama has won another four years in office","depth":7},{"id":115,"text":"to try to fulfill his election promises .","depth":7},{"id":116,"text":"Mr. Boehner said","depth":7},{"id":117,"text":"any deal with Mr. Obama must have the White House agree to lower spending on entitlement programs such as Medicare and Medicaid ,","depth":8},{"id":118,"text":"which take up an ever-increasing share of government spending .","depth":8},{"id":119,"text":"Grover Norquist , head of Americans for Tax Reform ,","depth":11},{"id":120,"text":"which sponsors an influential no-new-taxes pledge","depth":12},{"id":121,"text":"to which many Republicans are beholden ,","depth":12},{"id":122,"text":"said","depth":10},{"id":123,"text":"the revenue deal","depth":11},{"id":124,"text":"Mr. Boehner is offering","depth":11},{"id":125,"text":"passes muster .","depth":10},{"id":126,"text":"\" I heard the speaker say again and again ,","depth":12},{"id":127,"text":"let ' s not raise taxes ,","depth":13},{"id":128,"text":"let ' s have economic growth , \"","depth":13},{"id":129,"text":"Mr. Norquist told The .","depth":11},{"id":130,"text":"He said","depth":11},{"id":131,"text":"raising growth to 4 percent a year , up from the 2 percent","depth":13},{"id":132,"text":"that","depth":15},{"id":133,"text":"he said","depth":15},{"id":134,"text":"Mr. Obama has struggled to hit ,","depth":14},{"id":135,"text":"would mean an additional $ 5 trillion in tax revenue over 10 years .","depth":12},{"id":136,"text":"He said","depth":10},{"id":137,"text":"that comes","depth":12},{"id":138,"text":"without raising tax rates ,","depth":12},{"id":139,"text":"but still would give Mr. Obama solid revenue numbers","depth":13},{"id":140,"text":"to point to","depth":13},{"id":141,"text":"- though it ' s unlikely the CBO ,","depth":14},{"id":142,"text":"which keeps official score of legislation ,","depth":14},{"id":143,"text":"would calculate it that way .","depth":13},{"id":144,"text":"\" We ' re trying to get the president to actually put something down in writing and to engage in governing","depth":8},{"id":145,"text":"So let ' s take it a step at a time .","depth":10},{"id":146,"text":"This is new to him , \"","depth":10},{"id":147,"text":"Mr. Norquist said .","depth":9},{"id":148,"text":"Mr. Obama ran for re-election on a call","depth":7},{"id":149,"text":"to raise income tax rates on Americans with the highest incomes ,","depth":8},{"id":150,"text":"while holding rates low for everyone else .","depth":8},{"id":151,"text":"Republicans , though , said","depth":7},{"id":152,"text":"raising taxes on the wealthy amounted to a tax increase on small businesses .","depth":7},{"id":153,"text":"Mr. Boehner pointed back to discussions","depth":6},{"id":154,"text":"he had with Mr. Obama last year , during the height of the debt showdown ,","depth":6},{"id":155,"text":"when he said","depth":6},{"id":156,"text":"they talked about a deal","depth":7},{"id":157,"text":"that would lower tax rates","depth":8},{"id":158,"text":"but close enough loopholes","depth":9},{"id":159,"text":"to bring in more money into federal accounts .","depth":9}],"relations":[{"parent":319,"left":165,"right":318,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":165,"left":161,"right":164,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":161,"left":0,"right":1,"relation":"purpose","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":164,"left":2,"right":163,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":163,"left":3,"right":162,"relation":"condition","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":162,"left":4,"right":5,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":318,"left":268,"right":317,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":268,"left":179,"right":267,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":179,"left":173,"right":178,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":